 (Wikipedia)..Swedish company Interdynamic AB of Stockholm designed the Interdynamic MP-9 9mm submachine gun. Intended as a cheap submachine gun based on the Carl Gustav M/45 for military applications, Interdynamic did not find a government buyer, so it was brought to US market as open-bolt semi-automatic KG-9 pistol. title: For Sale:  Sale/Trade: Open Bolt .45/9mm Carbine, Demro Wasp
postcontent: Open Bolt .45 ACP Demro carbine, uses M-3 Grease Gun magazines (still cheap and still available). Can be converted to 9 MM using STEN Magazones by changing bolt head, barrel, and installation of a magazine well adapter. These parts are still available (I will sent the buyer to the source for them). The Demro carbine was one of the last of the open bolt designs made before the BATF ruled any further production of them to be a machine gun. These are not a NFA item, but are kissing cousins. Many were legally converted and registered pre-May 1986, leaving unconverted ones like this one rare collectors items. If you are an 07 FFL with a Class II SOT you can convert this to full auto in about five minutes without a permanent receiver modificvation, and then de-convert it and remove it from the NFA register when you surrender your license without needing to destroy the receiver. If you are not an 07 FFL with a Class II SOT you can enjoy ownership of a very neat plinking carbine that will always appreciate in value, as no more open bolt carbines can be produced. This one is in very good condition, shoots well, and is provided with one M-3 magazine. Unlike other "high capacity" magazines, there was not a run on M-3 mags, and they are available cheaply from several sources. In addition you can swap barrel and bolt head in about 5 minutes to a 9mm set, slip in a magazine well adapter, and shoot 9mm using STEN mags. Wire stock folds, and removes to become a magazine loader. I am not highly motivated to sell for cash, but prefer mature and high quality trades of equal value. Propose offers, don't waste my time with immature "tacti-cool" SKS's with kitchen sinks bolted on, or other childish stuff. Will consider quality tactical rifles, precision AR-15 flat top rifle, .300 Blackout rifle, WW-II era military rifles (unaltered, no sporters), or a high quality 5.56mm or 7.62mm precision bolt action rifle. My lowest preference is cash. You must have a Wisconsin CCW for local FTF sale, or transfer thru an FFL at your expense.
